Name: Blackcomb Equity LLC
Title: REFocusMaps
Description: REFocusMaps is a computer program designed for use by Real Estate Investors and anyone in the Real Estate field.  The program is designed for use on the web and on mobile devices.  The purpose of the program is to aid those in the Real Estate field in preforming market research and analysis.  Users of the program will be able to create custom maps of property data based on the state and zip codes they are working in.  Once the data has been mapped, the user will have a variety of helpful tools to assist them in their market analysis and assessment.  Basic features are to include, but not limited to, extensive data import options and data validation options, filtering data based on data parameters, sorting data and visualizing data in different ways based on data parameters, favoriting specific data points, selecting groups of data, providing meta data on selected groups of data or favorited data points, saving the state of the map, such as map center, map zoom, applied filters, applied and visual aids, to aid in ease of use, and exporting data based on filters, groups, and favorites.  More advanced features are to include, but not limited to, automatic data cluster finding via custom genetic algorithms to aid in identifying favorable markets, automatic value approximations via custom tailored algorithms to aid in market assessment, manual entry of data points, ability to share data and user maps with other users, ability to communicate with other users that are working in the same, or neighboring, zip codes.  Pricing will be based on a basic and pro subscription where a pro subscription will allow access to more features for an increased monthly cost.  Annual pricing will also be available.  Extensive user guides and FAQs will also be provided on the website and mobile applications to ensure users are able to effectively use the program.
Copyright_Claimant: Blackcomb Equity LLC. Address: 860 Ridgedale Ave, Birmingham, MI, 48009.

Title: The Mystery Body of Christ in the Old Testament: How the Bereans could Understand Romans 16:25-27 From the Scriptures of the Prophets
Description: The Apostles James, Peter, and Paul give us the keys to understand how the Mystery Body of Christ is revealed in the Old Testament. By following the words of the apostles we know that the union of Gentiles and Jews is associated with the rebuilding of the Tabernacle of David. The Apostles Paul and Peter equated the human body to a tent or tabernacle. When need to look to the Old Testament to see where two distinct groups of people depicted as the people of God are entering into a sanctuary pitched by God. We believe the Mystery Body of Christ is revealed in the book titled after Jesus. It will be depicted in the same place where God said He formed the human body and will be formed in the same manner which God said He would form His sanctuary.

Name: Smith, Grant Elliot
Title: Rathen
Description: The genre of the book is Fantasy Adventure. A king (Mathyus) and his two sons (Magom and Tyus) create a secret guild to seek magical ways to live forever. The king eventually dies and the sons fight for control of the wealthy kingdom with their magic and conjured beasts until the remaining members of the guild cover the castle with a magic protection shell. Spending two hundred years in the shell, each son gives his mortality to become immortal. Magom becomes an undead lich while Tyus trades his own heart for a demon heart. The brothers continue to fight and seek a way out of the shell. The demon brother sends out waves of summoned minions to terrorize the area where finally groups of adventurers are sent to kill the minions and find out where they are coming from. When adventurers fail to return the surrounding kingdoms hire people down on their luck. A group of twelve unlikely heroes adventure into the ancient castle and are able to defeat the two brothers. The main character is Rathen, who once had a position in a kingdomâ€™s army as a captain and become a drunk after he lost his job and now lives in a desolate little town. Rathenâ€™s closest ally is Bulo who also served as a soldier in the same army, who once was a gladiator and is now a tavern keeper. Other group members are Vyth, Vargas, Hammerbeard, Itlot, Boder, Efler, Fithian, Bandark, Zeller and a one-armed half-orc named Thack.  A running theme in the novel is of a prophecy that Rathen will be betrayed by a group member and that the nightmares that plague his mind of the lich are real.

Name: Simmons, William Edward
Title: The Last Mystery in the Bible: The King of Kings Reveals the Seven mountains Where Mystery Babylon Sits
Description: The Last Mystery in the Bible deals with one of the most important prophetic chapters in the Bible. Revelation 17 has been called one of the most difficult chapters to understand. This book contends the seven mountains where Mystery Babylon sits are seven mountains revealed in the Bible by Jesus. This book focuses on the meaning of the word ?Mystery? throughout the Bible. It focuses on the biblical meaning of the mountain-symbol throughout the Bible. This book refutes the Rome/ Roman emperor interpretation of Revelation 17. The seven mountains and seven kings reveal the focus and the hierarchy of satanic throughout the ages. The seven mountains are seven actual mountains revealed in the Bible by King Jesus, but the seven mountains spiritually symbolize spiritual principalities. The seven kings symbolize seven actual kingdoms, which arise to rule over the seven mountains, but the seven kings also symbolize the rulers of these kingdoms. The seven mountain revealed in the Bible follow the pattern of the Sabbath seen with the other groups of seven in the book of Revelation.

Name: LOMBARD-CLARK, CAROL
Title: CAROLINEâ€™S DREAM
Description: The Work is a documentary motion picture about the effects of war and post-traumatic stress disorder, with a particular focus on the Vietnam War, and the need for peace and efforts to achieve peace throughout the world. The producer, director, narrator and principal actress is Carol Lombard Clark and part of the story is her autobiography. Carol?s boyfriend was killed in action in Vietnam when Carol was in high school. The documentary reports on Carol?s travels back to Vietnam with Steve Roberts, the brother of her boyfriend John Roberts, to memorialize where John had died. Carol also reports on similar stories of other Vietnam War veterans and how they have coped with the aftereffects of the war, as well as how various groups of Vietnamese citizens have coped since the end of the war. Featured interviews include Carol?s husband, Dr. Douglas McAllister, who is also a producer; Vietnam veterans David McAllister, Doug?s brother, and Doug Howell; as well as Irene and Roland Lafayette, and Tony Cardinale Sr. and Tony Cardinale Jr., family members of other U.S. soldiers killed in Vietnam; and various Vietnamese citizens. Filmed on site in Maine; Washington, DC; Boston, Massachusetts; New York, NY; Vermont; Arizona; Vietnam; Israel; and India.

Title: "54" or "#54"
Description: Literary work in book form. 54 is a futuristic fictional sports drama about a genetically engineered star athlete whoâ€™s at the height of his career, but struggling to find his true purpose in life. 54 is considered the best genetically engineered football player to date. He also has the only female Sponsor, (Elizabeth Poe). Elizabeth is one of the East Sponsors has only 1 athlete, (54) even though her Sponsor license permits 15 created players. Sponsors are divided into 4 groups of 10. Each group represent a direction, North, South, East, West and consist of 4 teams. 16 teams total make up the NEFL. Sponsors create and support each of their "man made" creations. A Sponsor acts as both guardian and owners of their created player(s), but within certain guidelines and a contract which becomes active at players 17 year. 40 "Sponsors" make up the "National Engineered Football League" (NEFL). Sponsors control all aspects of sports, entertainment, business, money(NEFL Gambling/Players Coins), etc. ). All genetically created players are given a number with acts in place of legal name. A players number is NEVER duplicated. Each created player has coins issued with this number and their likeness, These are called "Players Coins". NEFL Gambling or "Players Coins" is a legal form of gambling permitted and regulated through the NEFL. These coins can appreciate and depreciate based on players performance during the season, closely resembling fantasy football and the stock market. After the tragic death of 54â€™s best friend and fellow team mate (85), 54 begins to question the morality of genetic engineering, its place in sports, and his role in the league and on the field. Name: Rose Media Entertainment Group, Inc.
Title: The Paladin Chronicles Talin Brightbanner:  The Sword
Description: Genre:  Epic Adventure; Subject Matter:  An eternal game of chess between the Great God and a hidden, unseen opponent on a world where men and demons will ultimately collide.  Talin Brightbanner, a blacksmith who is chosen by a goddess to be her champion, must stand and defend the world of Haarka from an otherworld invasion by demonic forces.  As demon soldiers continue to trickle onto his world, it is discovered that this demon army is not an invading army; rather, it is a retreating army that is being pushed back in a conflict that is raging in another location.  The first waves of demons are deserters of a much larger force.  Pursuing them are members of their own military who are hunting them to press them back into military duty.  Hunting both groups of demons is the enemy that is in an active state of war with them.  The world of Haarka is simply a falling-back point in an ages-old war between good and evil.  Caught in the middle of this eternal conflict is Talin Brightbanner; his calling by the Great God and his mate, the Great Goddess, to preserve his world from the destruction that is inevitable.  The demons are non-corporeal; they do not possess physical bodies but will inhabit the bodies of other beings and use them as their own war machines with which they pilot and fight.  Talin, assisted by other holy warriors called paladins, will soon gather to unite their strength.  Notwithstanding the tremendous power that the paladins wield, they ultimately find their way to the fortress city of Northgate where they are met by the prophet of the Church of the Great God.  A chilling message is given to Talin when he is told by the Great Goddess, "Build me an army." Tagline:   Can a band of heroes conquer a demon army if they have yet to conquer themselves?

Name: Verbiest, Thibault
Title: Amalek
Description: A Novel of fiction: Can a special unit of Tsahal (Israel Army of Defense aka IDF) have the ability to free the Auschwitz extermination camp?  Summary  In a part of the Middle East where there is complete chaos, an extremist group in an Egyptian secret shelter start to prepare to make nuclear attacks on Israel. Because the Hebrew country is isolated from the international community, it can only count on themselves to prevent attacks.  Two options are available to them: launch a preventative nuclear strike, or send an elite special unit to the south of Egypt using an experimental transportation technology. 10 men and women, hand picked from the elite groups of the country, volunteer for a mission which has an improbable chance to succeed. They have 12 hours to avoid a nuclear war. The squad is teleported, but the destination is not that expected. They are some kilometers from Auschwitz, in the year 1943? A narrator (whose identity stays unknown until the end of the story) recounts his memories: more than 20 years since a mission so unusual and not written in any history book.

Name: Larson, Stephen James
Title: Lighthouse
Description: LOG LINE: Lighthouse, the novel, is a story about Stephen Bjork who tries to carry the Christian message to a cynical gay community while longing for the one he loved during his adolescence.   Chapter 1 is about Stephenâ€™s death from brain cancer.  He dies in a hospice in Nyack, New York, the town he grew up in.  His 76 year old mother is by his side when he dies.  His mother moved to NY from Puerto Rico after her brother was killed by gay bashers.   The following chapters are about Stephenâ€™s life, it flashes before his eyes in an instant as he stands before God.   Stephen met Adam during their adolescence.  The two boys had a romantic (kissing only) affair, which ended abruptly when Adam?s father caught them kissing.  Stephen was able to remain on the soccer team, but Adam could not - Stephen felt he betrayed Adam during this decision.  Stephen?s mother tells Stephen that puppy love is not real and that if you truly love somebody God will find a way for the two of you to be together.   Stephen attends Bethany College in Lindsborg, KS.  He tries heterosexuality, but is lonely and feels guilty during this affair with a girl.  Stephen meets Olivia who is teaching a course on religion where she shows how the bible has been used to subjugate various groups of people (e.g. blacks, women).  Stephen feels a calling from God to use his writing talent to show the gay community how it is only one group that has received unfair treatment by religious people.  His goal is to entice homosexuals to embrace Christianity.   During the entire book Stephen misses Adam terribly.  He feels his mother was dead wrong about puppy love.  It is hard for Stephen to move on to other intimate/sexual relationships during his life ? he still loves Adam.  At the end of the book, Stephen and Adam get married in heaven before God ? Olivia performs the ceremony.

Name: Laloux, Frederic
Title: The Week
Description:
The Week is a three hour documentary educational and community screening series being developed to educate communities, corporations, and students into the realities and affects of Climate Change through a multipart - facilitated viewing experience. Each episode features eight key characters from the US and Europe who have experienced Climate Change first hand and are actively addressing what it means to them individually. The series will be published digitally and screened in person. The films will include original scripting, original principal photography, animation, stock imagery, and archival footage. 

The Week takes groups of people, within their existing social circles (groups of friends, colleagues, fellow worshippers) through a carefully guided journey that helps them reckon deeply with the reality of climate breakdown. Results from our prototypes are remarkable: people are deeply moved and changed, take up joyful action and invite more friends and colleagues to join, promising exponential reach.

We?ve tested the approach with leaders of large climate movements, as well as large corporations, CEO networks and faith movements. Their enthusiasm bodes well for the potential of creating an unprecedented coalition to help millions of people join the climate mobilization.
Copyright_Claimant: The Week ASBL. Address: 13 Rue Eigenhuis, Brussels, 1170, Belgium.

Description: Computer Program: Nature: A desktop application with a background canvas containing multiple, open, boxes which are text and image editors. These can be zoomed into and out of to provide editing (box level) and overall view of all boxes (zoomed out). Boxes editable at all zoom levels. The system also allows background images to provide memory aids for groups of boxes. Exports box data as pdf, htm and rtf (ebook) format. Boxes can be selected and grouped; made transparent and semi-transparent. Slide Show - as boxes can also be numbered. Multiple groupings allowed, so multiple slideshows performed on collection of boxes. The whole system is saved under one name, with all parts (boxes, zoom levels etc). Purpose: It allows writers, bloggers, any user of word processors, to have multiple documents open at the same time for comparison and editing.  Arrangement narrative and memory aid. Art works or business publications in the resident file format (.sto).  Uses for creative writing, education, business or other presentations, filing of complete works (many boxes of text/image)  in one save that can be sent. Functions: Open new application Add boxes (editors); delete boxes; resize boxes; Add content (text/image - paste/write); load image from computer. Drag boxes around background to enable useful and expressive positioning. Zoom whole background to edit boxes or inspect. Zoom out to view whole arrangement. Save/load. Export in common formats for publication. Slideshow. Display various groupings of boxes for different uses. Particular organization or structure in which the program has been created: Object orientated; standard systems. The computer language in which it is written: Windows: C#  Mac/Linux: Java Published as: Downloaded desktop application with an installer. Version: Lite version (sub set) and  Turbo version with all features Mobile version for phones/pads. Shared online groupware version for multiple concurrent users.

Title: Gloria Patri  - Carillon Music Scheduler
Description: Computer system application, all source codes and computer screens shall carry the name in Latin Gloria Patri meaning Glory to Our Father. Application shall allow the playing of religious Carillon music and by default, the music to be played at specific times will ?Westminster? bells playing Quarter Chime, Half Chime and an Hour Chime playing a melody consisting of four groups of four notes. Then it counts out the time by striking a larger bell as many times as whatever time it is.  It shall allow a user with little or no computer background to reprogram the Westminster bell melody with other musical compositions stored in separate file within the application.  The app. will provide for storing recorded musical pieces from various sources such as CD?S and others down-loadable media. In storing musical entries, files should be capable to accept store/use various standard and common formats. All music is to be stored in the system and capable to insert through direct input up to 4 categories for each musical composition.  All files will be accessed by the user for maintenance purposes; computer screens to be used will be limited to 10 or less. Programming logic will be minimal but effective enough to make the operation as intuitive as possible.  All wordings on the various screens will be in English and Spanish, allowing as well for the insertion other languages in the future.  Computer screen will be loaded based on the language requirements of the end-user. System shall also provide for the insertion of a photograph and/or display name, City, State and/or Country of the church/institution where system will reside. A logo/image will also be displayable to convey a religious meaning. There will be attachments to this document containing greater details concerning edits, draft computer displays, a glossary of terms and definitions to be used in programming the application.  Fields/Edits for maintaining schedules and musical compositions will apply
